        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(workboard): add worker dispatch CLI",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Start ready Workboard cards from dispatch by claiming a bounded batch and launching Gateway subagent worker runs with persisted session/run metadata.\n- Add `openclaw workboard` CLI plus `/workboard` slash command parity for list, show, create, and dispatch.\n- Expand Workboard plugin docs and add a dedicated CLI reference covering SQLite state, dispatch behavior, permissions, fallback, JSON redaction, and troubleshooting.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm test extensions/workboard -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/workboard/src/card-lookup.ts extensions/workboard/src/cli.ts extensions/workboard/src/cli.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/command.ts extensions/workboard/src/command.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/dispatcher.ts extensions/workboard/src/dispatcher.test.ts`\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- `env -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed` reached extension lint after typecheck; latest `origin/main` broad extension lint currently reports pre-existing unsafe-assertion findings outside this PR (for example qqbot/codex/line plus existing Workboard store/sqlite/tool files). Touched Workboard CLI/dispatcher files were linted directly above.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Workboard dispatch can now start bounded subagent worker lanes, and operators can inspect/create/dispatch cards from CLI or slash command surfaces.\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on the rebased branch.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm test extensions/workboard -- --reporter=verbose`; targeted Workboard `run-oxlint`; docs list/format checks; autoreview.\nEvidence after fix: Workboard extension suite passed 7 files / 94 tests, including dispatcher worker-start, slash write-scope, CLI claim-token redaction, explicit Gateway target fallback, and ambiguous prefix tests; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: Ready cards are claimed and receive persisted worker run metadata; claim tokens are redacted from new CLI JSON read paths; explicit remote Gateway dispatch failures do not mutate local state.\nWhat was not tested: A live provider-backed subagent run from a real Gateway was not exercised locally; unit tests cover the subagent runtime call and Workboard state transitions.\n",
